10246679742.name: Philadelphia Marathon 2023!!!
10246679742.description:
Ahh Philadelphia 🥳🥳🥳🥳

Congrats to my sister Sol Salgado that finished her first marathon in 3.20. I am sorry I did not run with you... At the end you did not need a pacer, you looked strong and finished like a rocket, you are the best 

I did not run a PR today (30 seconds!!! 30!!), but considering that I just ran NYC two weeks ago, I will take this as my best marathon performance to date :) 

And thanks to the whole PRTC. I joined the team a year ago, knowing that I needed to run with fast people to get stronger and faster, and here we are a year later, stronger and faster. We keep going 💪🏽💪🏽💪🏽

So yes, you can run NYC and then run Philly... It really hurts now hahaha

10166304722.name: NYC Marathon 2023!!
10166304722.description:
What a fantastic race on an unforgiving and relentless course, definitely the hardest I have ran so far. It is not necessarily the bridges, that you can prep for that, but the continuous ups and downs that really get you... Or got me at least. 
Official results: 2.51.29

I went out at the pace I was expecting to be, took the bridges at the speed I planned, but the other hills, specially around Central Park, were a killer. This is the first time I thought: if I cramp now, I will not be able to finish. The last mile was really hard 😅

Having said that, WHAT A RACE!! The crowds, the noise, the whole atmosphere, it is really great. I even had the chance to meet my fav YouTubers Ben Bridges Ben Parkes and Sarah Place :) 

Thanks so much to my wife that gives me the chance to be here and run as much as I want: she is the best :) 

Now back to work, ... But wait wait, in two weeks I will be running the beautiful streets of Philadelphia with the best of the Salgado/Ibanez, Sol Salgado :)
Or maybe I recover quick and really try to race again hahaha!? 😬😬😬
